cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as semantic role labeling.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes the use of graph convolutional networks (GCNs) for encoding constituent structures and improving the SRL system.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with improving the performance of an AI system for NLP tasks.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper proposes the use of neural networks (GCNs) for improving the SRL system.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category as the paper does not deal with visual data, but the use of GCNs for encoding structures could be relevant to some computer vision tasks.
